### Initialize shadcn/ui in a Vite project using npx

Source: https://github.com/shadcn-ui/ui/blob/main/apps/v4/content/docs/installation/vite.mdx

This command uses `npx` to run the `shadcn@latest init` command, specifically targeting a Vite project. It sets up the necessary configuration files and dependencies for shadcn/ui components in a standard project structure.

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init -t vite
```

--------------------------------

### Configure shadcn/ui components.json file

Source: https://github.com/shadcn-ui/ui/blob/main/apps/v4/content/docs/installation/manual.mdx

This JSON configuration file defines how shadcn/ui components are integrated into a project. It specifies styling, whether to use React Server Components (RSC), TypeScript (TSX) usage, Tailwind CSS settings (config path, CSS file, base color, CSS variables, prefix), path aliases for components and utilities, and the icon library to use. This file is crucial for customizing the component setup and ensuring proper imports and styling.

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://ui.shadcn.com/schema.json",
  "style": "radix-nova",
  "rsc": false,
  "tsx": true,
  "tailwind": {
    "config": "",
    "css": "src/styles/globals.css",
    "baseColor": "neutral",
    "cssVariables": true,
    "prefix": ""
  },
  "aliases": {
    "components": "@/components",
    "utils": "@/lib/utils",
    "ui": "@/components/ui",
    "lib": "@/lib",
    "hooks": "@/hooks"
  },
  "iconLibrary": "lucide"
}
```

--------------------------------

### Enable CSS Variables for Theming in components.json

Source: https://github.com/shadcn-ui/ui/blob/main/apps/v4/content/docs/(root)/theming.mdx

Illustrates the configuration required in `components.json` to enable CSS variables for theming in shadcn/ui. Setting `tailwind.cssVariables` to `true` is essential for the utility classes to correctly resolve to your defined CSS variables.

```json
{
  "style": "new-york",
  "rsc": true,
  "tailwind": {
    "config": "",
    "css": "app/globals.css",
    "baseColor": "neutral",
    "cssVariables": true
  },
  "aliases": {
    "components": "@/components",
    "utils": "@/lib/utils",
    "ui": "@/components/ui",
    "lib": "@/lib",
    "hooks": "@/hooks"
  },
  "iconLibrary": "lucide"
}
```

--------------------------------

### Install shadcn/ui Chart Component

Source: https://github.com/shadcn-ui/ui/blob/main/apps/v4/content/docs/components/base/chart.mdx

Provides instructions for installing the shadcn/ui chart component, covering both the command-line interface (CLI) method and manual installation steps including dependency installation and adding essential CSS variables for theming.

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add chart
```

```bash
npm install recharts
```

